# Project Overview

Next.js 16 template using React 19, Tailwind CSS v4, and shadcn/ui (new-york style).

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, React Server Components by default)
- **UI Library**: shadcn/ui v3 (new-york style), Radix UI primitives
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with CSS variables for theming, tw-animate-css for animations
- **Animation**: motion/react (Framer Motion)
- **Icons**: lucide-react
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Project Structure

- `app/` — Next.js App Router (pages, layouts, global CSS)
- `components/ui/` — shadcn/ui components (Button, Badge, etc.)
- `components/layout/` — Layout primitives (Stack, Grid, Cluster, Center, Split, Switcher)
- `components/animations/` — Animation wrappers (FadeIn, SlideInFromTop)
- `components/system/` — System/utility components (ProjectVersion)
- `lib/` — Utility functions (`cn()` helper)
- `types` — Shared type definitions (`BaseComponentProps`, `PropsWithClassName`)

## Key Conventions

- **Component Size**: Max 100 rows per file. Break into smaller components if exceeded.
- **Hooks**: Minimize `useEffect` use; prefer derived state, event handlers, or custom hooks.
- **Imports**: Use `@/` path alias for all imports
- **Class merging**: Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for merging Tailwind class names
- **Layout components**: Accept `BaseComponentProps` from `@/types`
- **shadcn/ui**: Add new components via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- **Fonts**: Geist Sans and Geist Mono via `next/font/google`

## Commands

- `pnpm dev` — Start development server
- `pnpm build` — Production build
- `pnpm lint` — Run ESLint
- `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <name>` — Add a shadcn/ui component
